Video Designer features a clean and intuitive UI, which makes creating and monitoring personalized videos (Pvideos) easy and accessible. The entire lifecycle of a Pvideo can be completed and monitored from this central application.

Read on to find out more about the UI of Video Designer.

## General navigation
![](data:image/png;base64,)

The UI of Pvideo Designer consists of three main regions:

- Top **toolbar** with search filters and action buttons (depending on selected vertical tab)

- Left **sidebar **with vertical tabs:

**Projects**: Landing page giving an overview and access to all existing Pvideo Projects

- **Mappings**: Overview and access to all existing Mappings that have been configured for a Project

- **Productions**: Finalized instances of Pvideos for monitoring purposes

- **Accounts and groups**: Displays the Projects of all accounts and groups to which you have access

- Central **work area** which displays the contents of the selected vertical tab

> **Tip: Collapsible sidebar**

If you need more screen space to comfortably view the contents of the selected vertical tab, you can collapse the sidebar by clicking the menu icon.

## Projects tab
The Projects tab is the landing page of Pvideo Designer. It displays all available Pvideo Projects in a fully searchable and sortable table. New Projects can be created, or existing Projects opened and edited in the video editor.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

## Mappings tab
The Mappings tab displays all available Pvideo Mappings in a fully searchable and sortable table. Any Mapping can be opened and edited from here.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

## Productions tab
The Productions tab displays all available Pvideo productions in a fully searchable and sortable table. The output of existing Pvideo productions can be downloaded from here, and new productions can be created.

The Productions tab is divided into two sections, depending on the configuration of the Pvideo project:

- **Dynamic **Pvideos contain CTA elements and follow a non-linear, user-directed timeline; the sequence of scenes may vary from user to user, depending on which choices they make during interaction with the Pvideo

- **Static **Pvideos are not user-directed and follow a linear timeline; the sequence of scenes may still vary from user to user, depending on the configuration of the Pvideo and how it resolves variable input data

Dynamic productionsStatic productions![](data:image/png;base64,) 

![](data:image/png;base64,)

## Editors
The Pvideo application consists of several different editor interfaces:

- **Project editor **for creating a Pvideo Project, consisting of a high-level **Storyboard editor** and a granular **Scene editor**

- **Mapping editor **for mapping video elements (for example, variable data fields) to the input data source

- **Production editor** for combining a Project with a data schema and source, producing a finished Pvideo

### Storyboard editor
The Storyboard editor consists of three main areas:

- Top **toolbar** with resource path and action buttons

- Left **sidebar** panel with all Scenes

- Central **work area** for connecting Scenes and creating a Storyline

Storyboard editor within the Project editor

![](data:image/png;base64,)Storyboard editor within the Project editor

### Scene editor
The Scene editor consists of three main areas:

- Top **toolbar** with resource path and action buttons

- Left **sidebar** panel with all Scenes

- Central **work area** for connecting Scenes and creating a Storyline

![](data:image/png;base64,)Scene editor within the Project editor

### Mapping editor
The Mapping editor consists of three main areas:

- Top **toolbar** with resource path and action buttons

- Left **sidebar** panel with all mappable elements within the Project

- Central **playback window** for replaying the Scene and map elements as they appear

![](data:image/png;base64,)Mapping editor

### Production editor
The Production editor consists of three main areas:

- Top **toolbar** with resource path and action buttons

- **Secondary toolbar** with an overall progress indicator of the Production

- Central **work area** for configuring the Pvideo Production

![](data:image/png;base64,)Production editor

Video Designer is a web-based video editing tool for creating interactive videos. It boasts a variety of innovative AI-powered features like script writing and text-to-speech (TTS). Video Designer is Doxees native solution for creating interactive videos and can be integrated seamlessly into the larger Doxee Platform workflow ecosystem to cover the entire lifecycle of interactive videos from creation to delivery and archiving.
